            </div>
            <hr>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="large-8 large-offset-2 columns">
                <p>The IDEA brand utilized two main colors along with black and white. The original branding was done to reflect a simple and clean look with a focus on photography. As time progressed, however, the designs representing IDEA moved away from photography and focused more on typographical compositions, utilizing the brand typefaces of Baskerville and Helvetica Neue.</p>
                <p>As website development progressed, we wanted to push the IDEA brand to add a layer of complexity to a stale brand to help the website feel more substantial. Prior to the redesign, the IDEA site felt too sparse and empty. By adding new colors and subtle patterns as the fifth element to the branding package we reached a solution that both teams were happy with.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

        <section class="project">
        <div class="row">
            <hr>
            <div class="large-8 large-offset-2 columns">
